<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-66-0575 </DOCNO><TEXT>Haemangioblastomas are rare polymorphic tumours with a predispositionfor the posterior cranial fossa, which explains the limitations of theCT diagnosis and the advantages of magnetic resonance imaging. MRI mustalways be interpreted cautiously, particularly because of the phenomenarelated to oedema. The use of paramagnetic contrast media is essentialin combination with a complete arteriographic assessment.</TEXT></DOC>